  "description": "Ambient strata. A single head moves across an 8-second reel at near-minimum bias, letting print-through and oxide build the texture while the signal rests. The ultra-slow LFO at 0.02Hz takes 50 seconds to complete one cycle — a geological breath. Sustained notes dissolve into reverberant oxide trails; the release outlasts most sequences.",
